text: Sybra striatopunctata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Sybra striatopunctata. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 7–11 mm long and 2⅔–3½ mm wide, and its type locality is Fauro Island, Solomon Islands. ==References== striatopunctata Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Sybra striatopunctata
